  "texts": [
    "FACS is an anatomicallybased comprehensive measurement system that evaluates 44 different muscle movements (e.g., raising of the eyebrows, tightening of the lips).",
    "The action units (AUs) of FACS are suitable for studying human naturalistic facial behavior as the thousands of anatomically possible facial expressions can be described as a combination of 27 basic AUs and multiple AU descriptors.",
    "Table 1 illustrates the descriptor for each action unit and the AUs that can be observed in basic emotions [32].",
    "Each AU corresponds to a specific facial movement, and different combinations of AUs represent different emotional expressions.",
    "Table 1 also presents the prototypical AUs observed in each basic emotion [33]."
  ],
